news.title: Vonovia to sell properties, consider new investors
news.para: It has earmarked 13 billion euros ($13.2 billion) worth of properties for sale and is looking into the possibility of new investors who could invest in its real estate portfolios, it said.

news.title: Norway paint maker Jotun exits Russia
news.para: Jotun, a global producer of paints and coatings, shut its Russian plant on March 3 following Moscow's invasion of Ukraine.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 415 crore worth assets of builders Avinash Bhosale, Sanjay Chhabria
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) had issued a provisional attachment order under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) on Tuesday to attach the assets of Bhosale, worth Rs 164 crore, while Chhabria's assets are worth Rs 251 crore.

news.title: The Executive Centre opens four centers with an investment of Rs 50 crore
news.para: While the two new centres in Bengaluru, located in UB City and Safina Towers will be operational this quarter, the centre in DLF Downtown Gurugram and Olympia Tech Park in Chennai will be operational in the last quarter of 2022.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder breaks into sealed flat, booked
news.para: Tilak Nagar police on Monday, based on a complaint of the collector’s office, booked the proprietor of Srinath Builders, Niraj Ved, for trespass and are looking for him.

news.title: Drone mapping done in 2,600 villages of Karnataka
news.para: So far, 2,664 villages have been mapped using drones. An MoU was signed between Karnataka’s Revenue department and Survey of India in February 2019.

news.title: Panchkula urban to have land pooling policy
news.para: A farmer will get 1,000 square yard residential and 200 square yard commercial plots in exchange of his land given for development of urban areas, according to the policy.

news.title: About 160 acres freed, 25 illegal colonies razed in Haryana in July: DTCP
news.para: These illegal colonies were carved out on agricultural land in Sohna, Bhondsi, Farukhnagar, Bilaspur, Kherki Daula and other areas.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body issues more challans than building plan approvals
news.para: After a year and only when the applicant moved the Punjab state information commission, officials from only zone A cared to reply, that from January 2019 to July 2021, it had cleared only 69 building plans but penalised 2,890 violators.

news.title: Renting out bungalow property in Lonavla? MTDC, civic council permissions a must
news.para: Senior inspector Sitaram Dubal of the Lonavla police said he had booked seven people under the IPC Section 188 (disobedience) because they had rented out bungalows without registering with the Maharashtra Tourism Development Corporation (MTDC) or LMC.

news.title: Noida: Paperwork scramble in last leg, Supertech twin towers ‘charging’ deferred
news.para: There is, as a result, no certainty on when ‘charging’ of the towers – the process to rig them with explosives – can begin, blurring timelines with less than three weeks left for the scheduled demolition on August 21.

news.title: Noida Expressway to shut for 30 minutes on Supertech twin towers demolition day
news.para: Traffic will be stopped at both ends of the expressway 15 minutes before the demolition and for the duration it takes for the dust to settle after the implosion, which is likely to be another 15 minutes.

news.title: Flexible workspace providers hiking rentals by up to 15%
news.para: The last few years have been a catalyst for large corporations to re-evaluate their priorities about workspace needs; flexibility and employee wellbeing have become priorities, and these conveniences come at a price.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing sells Rs 4,451 crore bad loans at a steep discount
news.para: The finance company sold its distressed portfolio in two tranches - ₹2,748 crore for ₹275 crore, equating to a recovery of 10 paise on a rupee, and ₹1,467 crore at ₹270 crore, equating to 18 paise of recovery for each rupee.

news.title: Adler overvalued real estate property by up to $239 million: Regulator
news.para: The Glasmacherviertel project to develop a former glassworks in Duesseldorf was valued at 375 million euros, and therefore overvalued by between 170 million and 233 million euros, the BaFin regulator said.
